gmd:title.gco:CharacterString: Hydro: (Polygon and Line) Green County, Wisconsin, 2017

gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: These polygon and line data layers represent hydrography for Green County, Wisconsin in 2017. They are feature classes within the geodatabase, Green_Hydro_2017.gdb. The features included in this geodatabase are' GREEN_BREAKLINES_2011', 'GREEN_HYDRO_UNK_LINE' , 'GREEN_HYDRO_UNK_POLY', and 'GREEN_HYDRO2_UNK_POLY',

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.

gmd:supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString:
Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements. For complete metadata documentation please visit http://www.co.green.wi.gov/localgov_departments_details.asp?deptid=115&locid=148 .
This data was submitted to the UW geospatial archive in 2017. Content may be considered current as of December 31, 2016. It was published to the UW geospatial archive as part of the Wisconsin Department of Administration Land Information Program annual collection of public data for the year 2017.
[GREEN COUNTY HAS MULTIPLE HYDRO DATASETS. FOR THIS GENERAL DATA REQUEST, WE ARE PROVIDING ALL WE HAVE EXCEPT ONES CLEARLY FROM THE WDNR. FOR ALL SUCH DATASETS, AT THIS POINT, CONTENT DATE OF DATA IS UNKNOWN.
FOR POLYGON-TYPE DATASETS, THERE WERE CLEARLY TWO DISTINCT DATASETS WITH DIFFERENT ORIGINS. BOTH ARE BEING PROVIDED. ORIGINS ARE UNKNOWN AT THIS POINT, BUT GREEN COUNTY OR ONE OF ITS CONTRACTORS LIKELY HAD A ROLE IN THE DEVELOPMENT OF AT LEAST ONE OF THEM.
ONE OF THE TWO HAD POLYLINE-TYPE DATASETS THAT CLEARLY WERE OF SIMILAR ORIGIN SINCE THE POLYLINE-TYPE DATASETS APPEAR TO ALIGN WITH THE POLYGON FEATURE PERIMETERS. BUT THE POLYLINE-TYPE DATASETS APPEAR TO ADDITIONALLY REPRESENT STREAM CENTERLINES AND/OR FLOWLINES. THE POLYGON-TYPE DATASET THAT ALIGNS WITH THE POLYLINE-TYPE DATASETS IS NAMED IN THIS DATA PROVISION, "GREEN_HYDRO_UNK_POLY." THE OTHER POLYGON-TYPE DATASET IS NAMED IN THIS DATA PROVISION, "GREEN_HYDRO2_UNK_POLY."
ONE OF THE POLYLINE-TYPE DATASETS WAS LABELED AS STREAMS-INTERMITTENT AND THE OTHER AS RIVERS-PERENNIAL. THE TWO HAVE BEEN COMBINED INTO ONE DATASET, "GREEN_HYDRO_UNK_LINE."
ALSO RELEVANT IS "GREEN_BREAKLINES_2011," PROVIDED AS A SEPARATE DATASET.]
